.\" Man page for arachna
.TH ARACHNA 1 "2026-06-09" "arachna 2.9.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
arachna \- context collector for AI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B arachna
[\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR]
[\fB\-\-all\fR]
[\fB\-\-clean\fR]
[\fB\-\-list\fR]
[\fB\-\-validate\fR]
[\fB\-\-doctor\fR]
[\fB\-\-init\fR]
[\fB\-\-install\-hook\fR]
[\fB\-\-presets\-update\fR]
.br
.B arachna \-\-completion
.RI [ bash | zsh ]
.br
.B arachna \-\-version
.br
.B arachna \-\-snapshot
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B arachna \-\-diff
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B arachna \-\-store
.RI [ gc | stats ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
arachna collects project files into token-limited chunks ready for AI consumption.
It understands tokens (not lines) and splits output smartly so nothing gets cut
in the middle.
.PP
It supports incremental diffs via snapshots: snapshot what an AI has seen,
then send only what changed. Works across multiple chats, agents, and sessions.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR
Collect a specific profile.
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Collect all profiles.
.TP
\fB\-\-clean\fR
Remove all collected files.
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
List available profiles.
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\fR
Validate configuration for errors. Exits 1 if problems found.
.TP
\fB\-\-doctor\fR
Run full configuration diagnostic.
.TP
\fB\-\-init\fR
Interactive .arachna.json bootstrap.
.TP
\fB\-\-init \-\-defaults\fR
Auto-detect project type and create config non-interactively.
.TP
\fB\-\-init \-\-preset\fR \fIname\fR
Use a specific preset for initialization.
.TP
\fB\-\-install\-hook\fR
Install post-commit git hook.
.TP
\fB\-\-install\-hook \-\-force\fR
Overwrite existing hook.
.TP
\fB\-\-presets\-update\fR
Fetch and merge presets from remote repository.
.TP
\fB\-\-presets\-update \-\-url\fR \fIurl\fR
Use custom URL for presets (must be http:// or https://).
.TP
\fB\-\-completion\fR \fIbash|zsh\fR
Generate shell completion script. Usage:
.RS
.B source <(arachna \-\-completion bash)
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Print version and exit.
.SS Watch Commands
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot\fR
Show usage hint for snapshot commands.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot list\fR
List all snapshots.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot create\fR \fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR \fB\-\-name\fR \fIid\fR
Create a named snapshot. \fIid\fR must match [\ew][\ew.\-]* (no path separators).
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot update\fR \fIid\fR [\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR]
Update an existing snapshot. Optionally change the profile.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot delete\fR \fIid\fR
Delete a snapshot. Objects survive for other snapshots.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot info\fR \fIid\fR
Show snapshot details.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot info\fR \fIid\fR \fB\-\-profile\fR
Show stored profile only.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot info\fR \fIid\fR \fB\-\-stats\fR
Show file and command counts only.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot rename\fR \fIold\fR \fInew\fR
Rename a snapshot.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff\fR
Diff from the single available snapshot (auto-select).
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-from\fR \fIid\fR
Diff from a specific snapshot against current state.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-from\fR \fIA\fR \fB\-\-to\fR \fIB\fR
Cross-snapshot diff between two snapshots.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-all\fR \fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR
Full project as diff — no snapshot needed.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-stat\fR
Show diff statistics only (counts, no content).
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-flat\fR
Flat output without grouping headers.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-format\fR \fIxml\fR
XML output format.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-mode\fR \fIstructural\fR
Block-level diff — understands code functions and classes.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-mode\fR \fIrepo\-map\fR
Repo-map diff — signatures only with change markers.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-compress\fR
Compress whitespace in diff output.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-output\-dir\fR \fIpath\fR
Write diff files to a custom directory.
.TP
\fB\-\-store stats\fR
Show content-addressable store statistics (snapshots, objects, dedup).
.TP
\fB\-\-store gc\fR
Garbage collect unreferenced objects from the store.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\-dir\fR \fIpath\fR
Directory for output files (default: arachna_context/).
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR, \fB\-v\fR
Show skipped files and compression stats.
.TP
\fB\-\-compress\fR
Compress whitespace to save tokens (collapses blank lines, strips trailing spaces).
Does not modify indentation.
.TP
\fB\-\-incremental\fR
Only collect files changed since last run. Uses smart hybrid cache
(mtime_ns + size + SHA256).
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fIxml|json\fR
Output format. Default is markdown.
.TP
\fB\-\-merge\fR
Append to existing output instead of replacing.
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Preview what will be collected without writing files.
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Force overwrite with \fB\-\-install\-hook\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-query\fR \fItext\fR
Filter files by query. Uses keyword scoring (+10 filename, +8 exports,
+5 imports, +3 content) and import chain (depth 2).
.TP
\fB\-\-mode\fR \fIfull|headers|repo\-map\fR
Collection mode.
.RS
.TP
full
Complete file contents (default).
.TP
headers
Full content with dependency/export headers.
.TP
repo\-map
Function/class signatures only (50-70% token savings).
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-pre\-commands\fR
Skip pre_commands for this run.
.SH SAFETY
Commands in .arachna.json run with shell=True — pipes, redirection, and
utilities like git, tree, and grep are available. You control the config
file, you are responsible for its contents.
.PP
Internal operations use a restricted sandbox: 11 safe commands, no shell
metacharacters, no file arguments. Protects against injection via snapshot
names, preset URLs, and external input.
.PP
Snapshot IDs are validated against path traversal. Tokenizer files are
checked for malicious code before import. Preset URLs are restricted to
http:// and https://.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBARACHNA_MAX_HASH_SIZE\fR
Maximum file size in bytes for SHA256 hashing during incremental collection.
Default: 10485760 (10 MB).
.TP
\fBARACHNA_SAFE_TOKENIZERS\fR
Comma-separated list of safe tokenizer module names. Default: tiktoken,transformers.
.TP
\fBARACHNA_PRE_COMMAND_DELAY\fR
Seconds to sleep between pre_commands. Default: 0 (no delay).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Create a config with auto-detected profiles:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-init \-\-defaults
.RE
.PP
Collect all profiles:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-all
.RE
.PP
Collect code profile, skip git history:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-profile code \-\-no\-pre\-commands
.RE
.PP
Create a snapshot and diff later:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-snapshot create \-\-profile full \-\-name baseline
.br
.I ... make changes ...
.br
.B arachna \-\-diff \-\-from baseline
.RE
.PP
Full project as repo-map diff:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-diff \-\-all \-\-profile code \-\-mode repo\-map
.RE
.PP
Filter by query:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-all \-\-query "authentication"
.RE
.PP
Generate shell completion:
.RS
.B source <(arachna \-\-completion bash)
.RE
.PP
Check configuration:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-validate
.br
.B arachna \-\-doctor
.RE
.PP
Store management:
.RS
.B arachna \-\-store stats
.br
.B arachna \-\-store gc
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI.arachna.json\fR
Project configuration with profiles.
.TP
\fIarachna_context/\fR
Default output directory for collected files.
.TP
\fI.arachna_cache.json\fR
Incremental mode cache (mtime_ns + size + SHA256).
.TP
\fI.arachna_manifest.json\fR
Manifest tracking all output files for cleanup.
.TP
\fI.arachna/\fR
Content-addressable store for Watch snapshots (auto-gitignored).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Error (invalid config, missing profile, validation failure, blocked command).
